![](https://pt.globalvoices.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/superdrag.jpg)

The animation _Super Drags_ recounts the story of three youths who transform
into drag queens by night. | Image: Netflix/ Public

In late May 2018, Netflix announced plans to
[launch](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ERQ9wN8uXWw) _Super Drags,_ the first
animation produced in Brazil. The
[story](https://emais.estadao.com.br/noticias/tv,netflix-anuncia-super-drags-
sua-primeira-serie-animada-brasileira,70002332706) features three youths who
work in a department store during the day and by night transform into [drag
queen](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drag_queen) superheroes.

Fans
[expressed](https://www.facebook.com/rupaulsdragrace/posts/10155579007492828)
excitement, but various conservative groups targeted the series with [fake
news ](https://emais.estadao.com.br/noticias/tv,animacao-super-drags-
incentiva-a-homossexualidade-em-criancas,70002407556)about its content.
According to a report by [O Estado de SÃ£o
Paulo](https://emais.estadao.com.br/noticias/tv,animacao-super-drags-
incentiva-a-homossexualidade-em-criancas,70002407556), one social media user
accused the cartoon of â€œprovoking homosexuality (sic) in childrenâ€ and â€œmaking
apologies for lesbianism (sic) and other sexual practices.â€

Netflix produces other animated series for adults such as [_BoJack Horseman_
](https://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/BoJack_Horseman)and _[Rick and
Morty,](https://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rick_and_Morty)_ but _Super Drags_ was
the first to spark controversy.

The Brazilian Paediatrics Society ([Sociedade Brasileira de
Pediatriaâ€“](http://www.sbp.com.br/imprensa/detalhe/nid/contra-a-exposicao-de-
criancas-e-adolescentes-a-conteudos-improprios-na-tv/)SBP) published an
official statement condemning the animation, saying that it â€œregards with
concernâ€ that _Super Dragsâ€™_ will be available to children on Netflix:

> A SBP respeita a diversidade e defende a liberdade de expressÃ£o e artÃ­stica
